                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            Statue brought from Pōlakam (Pondicherry). A certain Nāyakattār Āṇṭāṇ Kōtai, alias Kulōttuṅka-rāyaṇ consecrated the image of Tiruvātavūr-Nāyaṉār (Māṇikkavācakar) at the temple of Pōlakam and donated lands for food offerings and the maintenance of sacred lamps.
                        </summary> 
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
